Tutorial: Hello, Quarto

Some comments before the tutorial

  • The tutorial uses the Visual Editor in RStudio. We recommend to frequently switch between Visual and Source mode (the tutorial will explain how to do that) to see how the raw markdown syntax looks like.

  • Remember to put all .qmd files you download during the tutorial into the RStudio project directory you have created earlier.

  • Skip watching the video introduction for now (the video is great, but too long for the 2h workshop).

Start the tutorial

If you have problems during the tutorial come back here and see the next section for our list of anticipated issues. After completing the first tutorial, come back here and continue with the next tutorial on this page.

Let’s start

Now you can start the first tutorial at https://quarto.org/docs/get-started/hello/rstudio.html.

Possible problems and related comments

  • The tutorial mentions the Markdown syntax (e.g. **bold**) used in Quarto but never gives you this link where the Pandoc Markdown syntax is described in-depth.

  • The tutorial discusses the format: html option in the YAML header and implies that you could also use pdf or docx. Unfortunately, format: pdf will not render for this particular .qmd document because the image of the penguins is added from an URL (you can see this when switching to Source mode), which for some reason does not work for pdfs…
    However, rendering with format: docx works and the result will look like this:
